2026-05-05 21:46:58,176 p=26178 u=root n=ansible | ERROR! We were unable to read either as JSON nor YAML, these are the errors we got from each:
JSON: Expecting value: line 1 column 1 (char 0)

Syntax Error while loading YAML.
  found character that cannot start any token

The error appears to be in '/root/linuxstack/playbooks/final_report.yml': line 44, column 1, but may
be elsewhere in the file depending on the exact syntax problem.

The offending line appears to be:

          - "RAM libre : {{ ansible_memfree_mb }} MB"
	  - "Disque    : {{ disk_result.stdout }} libres"
^ here
There appears to be a tab character at the start of the line.

YAML does not use tabs for formatting. Tabs should be replaced with spaces.

For example:
    - name: update tooling
      vars:
        version: 1.2.3
#    ^--- there is a tab there.

Should be written as:
    - name: update tooling
      vars:
        version: 1.2.3
# ^--- all spaces here.
We could be wrong, but this one looks like it might be an issue with
missing quotes. Always quote template expression brackets when they
start a value. For instance:

    with_items:
      - {{ foo }}

Should be written as:

    with_items:
      - "{{ foo }}"

